participants.verdict:
{
  "verdict": "reject",
  "conceptual_groups": [
    {
      "id": "group-1",
      "summary": "Freeze and terminal-state logic can bypass an active reviewer reject because the draft keys terminal outcomes only off \"material pushback\".",
      "severity": "blocking",
      "findings": [
        {
          "id": "f1",
          "description": "The `<guardrails>` definition of \"material pushback\" excludes an active `reject` verdict unless that reject depends on a `blocking` or `major` finding. In the source authority, freeze is allowed only after all reviewers are `approved` or `conditional`, and minor-item arbitration is allowed only after that point, so this definition is too weak as the sole freeze gate.",
          "source_section": "<guardrails>"
        },
        {
          "id": "f2",
          "description": "The `<completion>` predicates for `frozen`, `frozen_with_conditions`, `pushback`, and `resume_required` are driven by whether material pushback remains, not by whether any reviewer is still `reject`. That leaves a real state from the source architecture unresolved: a reviewer can still reject over a minor item, yet the draft can treat the run as freezable because no material pushback remains.",
          "source_section": "<completion>"
        },
        {
          "id": "f3",
          "description": "Step 3's self-check claims credibility for terminal-state validation by checking mutual exclusivity against the single material-pushback definition, but that check misses the reject-without-blocking/major case and therefore over-claims compliance.",
          "source_section": "<steps> Step 3"
        }
      ],
      "redesign_guidance": "Keep the blocking/major concept separate if needed, but add an explicit reviewer-status gate: `frozen` and `frozen_with_conditions` must require all active reviewers to be `approved` or `conditional` after any required `regression_sanity` pass. Then update `pushback` and `resume_required` so unresolved minor-only rejects still land in a non-frozen terminal state, and update the self-check to validate reviewer-status legality semantically rather than only reusing the material-pushback definition."
    }
  ],
  "fix_decisions": [],
  "residual_risks": [
    "Canonical package-path synchronization still depends on the basename-only package file summary staying aligned with the full promoted paths used in the draft.",
    "Budget-exhaustion handling is referenced from inherited architecture more than locally spelled out, so future edits could drift unless the terminal-state gate is tightened."
  ],
  "strengths": [
    "Authority is presented as an ordered operative chain and cleanly separated from runtime-scoped inputs and reference evidence.",
    "Canonical artifacts, canonical history, and run-scoped evidence are separated clearly with explicit lifecycle statements.",
    "Context gathering is correctly positioned as a precondition rather than a numbered workflow step.",
    "Carry-forward handling by finding or conceptual-group ID is explicit and mechanically stated.",
    "Decision-history preservation for `update` and `fix` is defined as append-only with prior history retained."
  ]
}
